  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test --optimize --optimize-runs 1000000 -v\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nToday, I have experienced an issue while running `forge test` by Github ci actions.\r\n\r\nIt tried to run the following command:\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge test --optimize --optimize-runs 1000000 -v\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd the error occurs:\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge clean && forge test --optimize --optimize-runs [10](https://github.com/my-project/my-repo/runs/6214574813?check_suite_focus=true#step:4:10)00000 -v\r\nerror: Found argument '--optimize-runs' which wasn't expected, or isn't valid in this context\r\n\r\n\tDid you mean '--optimizer-runs'?\r\n\r\n\tIf you tried to supply `--optimize-runs` as a value rather than a flag, use `-- --optimize-runs`\r\n\r\nUSAGE:\r\n    forge test --optimize --optimizer-runs <OPTIMIZER_RUNS>\r\n\r\nFor more information try --help\r\nmake: *** [Makefile:10: test] Error 2\r\nError: Process completed with exit code 2.\r\n```\r\n\r\nArgument `--optimize-runs` was changed to `--optimizer-runs` on the recent commit?",
